<h1 class="c1"><a name="h.k314ykjl47dc"></a><span>Administration</span></h1>
<p><a name="id.5mck4swmrsct" href="#"></a></p>
<h2 class="c1"><a name="h.y44viqx1yy3y"></a><span>Permissions Administration</span></h2>
<h2 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.4i3q4958azi"></a><span>Defining Permissions for an individual user</span></h2>
<p class="c1"><span>For every person in Methvin, you can determine:</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Will he or she be able to access Methvin?</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>What actions he/she will be able to perform.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>What parts of the system (which Projects, Documents, Workspaces) he/she will be able to access.</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1"><span>The first option (will the user be able to use Methvin),is a simple yes or no.</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>The second option can be quickly defined by the 'User Type, which pre-configures a set of common allowed actions and restrictions.</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>The third set of settings (what elements or parts of the system the user will be able to access) is determined at the time of:</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Adding or editing a new Member (Project, Workspace)</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Adding or editing the user.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><a name="id.fv4l5q2sp65r" href="#"></a></p>
<h2 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.bsdppbj6wcy8"></a><span class="c11">User Types</span></h2>
<p class="c1"><span>Defining a role on a user provides a preconfigured set of system permissions.</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>See the table below for a quick guide to the permissions defined by each role</span></p>
<p><a name="c471b3b442f1a709181c6033e70b47a21e8f6c95" href="#"></a><a name="1" href="#"></a></p>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="c30">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c25 c1">&nbsp;</p>
</td>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Quick description</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Super Administrator</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Can do everything</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Administrator</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Can do everything, except managing other administrators and super administrators</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Manager</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Can do everything on Clients, Projects and Workspaces for which administrators granted Management permissions</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Executive</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Can work on everything, but not setting permissions</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Estimator</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Can do everything on Projects and Workspaces (upload files, assign tasks, etc.)</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Project Manager</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Can work on Claims and view the tenders, but cannot set permissions</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Subcontractor</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Is a Customer that can work on his Quotation and submit it as a completed Quotation, but cannot access any of the main workspaces</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Supplier</span></p>
</td>
<td class="c13">
<p class="c10 c1"><span>Is a Customer that can work on his Quotation and submit it as a completed Quotation, but cannot access any of the main workspaces</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="c9">
<p class="c1 c10"><span>Guest</span></p>
</td>
