</table>
<h2 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.tgsngorl4bgx"></a><a name="id.k5fwpuvmim3k" href="#"></a><span class="c11">Permissions for Modules</span></h2>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Go to Administration tab &nbsp;and click on 'System Administration tab’ here you can select the user type from the drop down and manage their permissions.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Scroll down a bit and set up the permissions for the project, resources, workspace, etc in question, as it is shown in the following picture:</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1 c15 c31"><span class="c11 c14 c29">[Pic]</span></p>
<h4 class="c28 c1 c15"><a name="h.9l90qu6ikq32"></a><span class="c11 c32">Permissions categories:</span></h4>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>'None' → no permissions at all</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>'Read' → only see things and comment them. In case of tasks, only being able to complete tasks assigned to the person in question</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>'Read, Write &amp; Delete' → same as the previous option, but also being able to delete information</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1"><span>Note: Remember to save the changes after setting the permissions up!</span></p>
<h2 class="c1"><a name="h.3e792sorkbva"></a><span>Editing my company information</span></h2>
<h3 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.lyxrfdud9zy5"></a><span>Methvin allows you to do the following modifications:</span></h3>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Changing your company name</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Changing your company logo</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1"><span>In this section we will explore these features mentioned above.</span></p>
<h4 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.nvadqtdv6cqd"></a><span>Changing your company name</span></h4>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Go to the administration panel.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Select Company tab</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Click on 'Edit company info' on the Actions menu on your right, as shown below:</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Here you will be able to change the company name, as well as other information. Once you do so, please remember clicking on 'Save' to keep the changes.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Note: In case you changed the company name, you will have to press the F5 key to refresh the data and notice the new name.</span></li>
</ol>
<h4 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.ar24qm2i336t"></a><span>Changing your company logo</span></h4>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>We strongly suggest using a 600 px X 150 px logo of your company to use, otherwise it may not be displayed correctly.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Please bear in mind that system notifications will be using your logo when sent, otherwise, by default they will be sending a Methvin logo.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>If you have not never changed your logo at all yet, on the top left corner you may notice a picture as below (where [Company Name]) stands for your Company name.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>[Pic]</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Click on 'Change logo' and upload the picture you wish to use as a logo. Once again, we suggest using a 600×150 one.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>On the other hand, if you have already uploaded logo, but you wish to change it to a different one, you may do as following:</span></li>
</ol><ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Go to the administration panel.</span></li>
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Select 'Company tab'</span></li>
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Click on edit button then go to 'Company Logo' on the Actions menu on your right, as shown below:</span></li>
</ol>
<h2 class="c1"><a name="h.xmebogpipg0u"></a><span>Edit Users</span></h2>
<p><a name="id.9bvfu3n7t6x7" href="#"></a></p>
<h3 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.6tekwdjwi45u"></a><span>How to add a contact, user, or company in Methvin</span></h3>
<p class="c1"><span>When adding a person in Methvin you are doing one of two things:</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>You are creating a new user (so that they can access the system)</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Simply adding the contact information (for reference, subcontractor, supplier, etc)</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1"><span>For every person in Methvin you will at least have the contact information.</span></p>
<h3 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.dicyr0cqk6vo"></a><span>Adding a person</span></h3>
<h3 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.f90xcejhkvyn"></a><span>Create a new person in Methvin: simple steps</span></h3>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Administration Panel add</span></li>
</ol><ol class="c6" start="1">
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Add user</span></li>
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Add New Subcontractor</span></li>
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Add New Supplier</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1 c17 c25">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="c1"><span>You may also be able to create a new user as well by inputting all the data required, which you may notice inside the red perimeter in the previous picture.</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>The following are the fields you need to complete:</span></p>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>New person: New person name (i.e.: John Doe)</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Email: Email of the person you are adding (i.e.: <span id="cloak3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a">This email address is being protected from spambots. You need JavaScript enabled to view it.</span><script type='text/javascript'>
				document.getElementById('cloak3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a').innerHTML = '';
				var prefix = '&#109;a' + 'i&#108;' + '&#116;o';
				var path = 'hr' + 'ef' + '=';
				var addy3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a = 'j&#111;hn.d&#111;&#101;.' + '&#64;';
				addy3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a = addy3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a + 'M&#101;thv&#105;n' + '&#46;' + '&#111;rg';
				var addy_text3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a = 'j&#111;hn.d&#111;&#101;.' + '&#64;' + 'M&#101;thv&#105;n' + '&#46;' + '&#111;rg';document.getElementById('cloak3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a').innerHTML += '<a ' + path + '\'' + prefix + ':' + addy3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a + '\'>'+addy_text3eae8f2c1f01cf46209a828cb109057a+'<\/a>';
		</script>)</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Company: The company this person belongs to (i.e.: The Agency - Advertising Experts)</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>User type: This value will be used to limit the </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#id.fv4l5q2sp65r">user type</a></span><span>&nbsp;(i.e.: administrator)</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c1"><span>Example:</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>After you fill in all the details, please click on the 'save' button. Then, an email will be sent to the email you input so that the person can set up his own password.</span></p>
