<h3 class="c12 c1 c15"><a name="h.wsbjpkw6ee8s"></a><span>Administration Panel add</span></h3>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>Adding Methvin users on the administration panel.</span></p>
<p class="c25 c1">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>1. </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#id.5mck4swmrsct">Go to the administration panel</a></span><span>.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>2. Click on 'Users', and then on 'Add user'</span></p>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Or, for faster access. Click on the 'Add user' option directly in the Administration Panel</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c1 c37"><span>Input the Person basic data:</span></p>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c8 c1 c27"><span>Name</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>E-mail</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Make sure you are choosing the right Company for the person (not mandatory)</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Select whether you are simply adding contact information, or if the person will be able to access Methvin</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Make sure you are giving the right role/user type (the user type you chose will define the person default permissions</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.gtxiz3xxqyv1"></a><span>Providing access permissions to a person</span></h3>
<p class="c1"><span>There are two ways to provide access permissions to a person.</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20 c15">
<h3><a name="h.g44p0ewpr2tz"></a><span>Importing contacts through a .CSV file or a VCard file</span></h3>
</li>
</ol>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>Methvin provides you with the opportunity of uploading your contacts fairly fast and easy through the CSV or VCard file importation.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>In order to do so, you first have to enable the Contact Module (shown as People under tabs), which may come as disabled by default. - </span><span class="c0"><a class="c3" href="#id.k5fwpuvmim3k">how to enable a Module</a></span><span>&nbsp;-.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>Once you make sure it is enabled, please do as following:</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Access the Project, Pricing, Claims, Workspace, etc. where the contacts will be imported at</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Access the User tab</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Click on Import/Export, and select Import</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Select Persons</span></li>
<li class="c27 c8 c1"><span>Select whether you will be using a CSV file or a VCard file as shown below:</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<h4 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.liivw0aw9ol4"></a><span>CSV Importation</span></h4>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>You must first choose the file you will be using to import the contacts from. Important Notes</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c27 c5 c1"><span>You should not disable the option asking whether the first row contains fields names</span></li>
<li class="c27 c5 c1"><span>You may choose a different delimiter in case it is not a comma.</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>After selecting the files, please match the Methvin fields (on your left) with the fields brought by the file to be imported (on your right).</span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c1"><span>After making sure everything is alright, just click on Import.</span></p>
<h4 class="c37 c1 c15"><a name="h.z50a2rf3m5v4"></a><span class="c38">2. &nbsp;VCard Importation</span></h4>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>As above</span></p>
<h2 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.mtjdw5cj9rno"></a><span>Adding a company</span></h2>
<p class="c1"><span>Adding a 'Company' serves several purposes in Methvin:</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>Input of complex contact data for the company</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>It facilitates visibility of data to all users within the company group</span></li>
<li class="c1 c17 c20"><span>It enables to quick classification &nbsp;and accessibility of all the information related to the company</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c25 c1">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="c1"><span>To add a company in Methvin, you have to do the following steps:</span></p>
<h3 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.ro9g4j1v984i"></a><span>1. Go to the Administration tab</span></h3>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>Click on the link “Company tab”, and select Add.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<h3 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.vo2lt2bvjucn"></a><span>2. Create a New Company</span></h3>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>Click on the “Add” button, and select “Company”</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<h3 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.cjtjdcb5yfge"></a><span>3. Enter Company information</span></h3>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>Enter the Company information</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Enter all the relevant contact information that you have for the company</span></li>
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Finally, click on the “Add company” button.</span></li>
</ol>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>You will now see the company displayed in the navigation panel and in the dashboard. Like this:</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c20 c22"><span>Note: In some installations, the first company that is added may not be displayed right away. This only happens with the first company that you add. Hitting 'refresh' on your browser fixes this issue.</span></li>
</ol>
<h1 class="c1"><a name="h.clmqtvjv1d1p"></a><span>Documentation Module</span></h1>
<h2 class="c1 c15"><a name="h.1lhomxahujz6"></a><span>Documents</span></h2>
<p class="c1"><span>One of the key features of Methvin is that you can not only upload, download and share any type of document but that you can edit files online to a certain degree as well. We therefore distinguish between the document management features and the document editing features of Methvin.</span></p>
<h2 class="c1 c15 c21"><a name="h.bsmmfaqa05as"></a><span class="c11">List view</span></h2>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>In the list view of the Documents module you can see all files of the current project. Note the Edit button, and below Actions, some files have this and others don't. This distinguishes between files that are editable online and files that can just be downloaded.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1 c15"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.c6jlnzeoks3b"></a><span class="c11 c16">Actions</span></h3>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>When the Actions column in the list view is active you will notice that there are four different types of documents, with different options in this column:</span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>The first action (the arrow button) is available for most document types; it lets you download the currently selected files to your local hard drive. </span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>The rest is specific to a certain document type - Note the following examples.</span></p>
<ol class="c24" start="1">
<li class="c4 c1"><span>The standard document (for example a Word or a Photoshop file); this type of document can only be downloaded.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>The editable document; here you have the choice between downloading and editing.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>ZIP archive; you can unzip it directly on the server, or you can download it as you would any other document.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>PDF document which can be viewed on the screen or downloaded.</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.q9hvjbm10n0j"></a><span class="c11 c16">Toolbar </span></h3>
<p class="c1 c34"><span class="c14">[Pic]</span></p>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Upload a file: Lets you upload a file from your local hard drive to Methvin. This file can be of any type.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Document: Lets you create an online editable rich text document (which is stored as an HTML file).</span></li>
</ol><ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Update file: Allows you to update the selected file.</span></li>
</ol><ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Delete: This removes the file from the database</span></li>
</ol><ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Mark as read: Marks the selected file(s) as read.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Mark as unread: Marks the selected file(s) as unread.</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.y4hylyfztnts"></a><span class="c11 c16">Detail view</span></h3>
<p class="c1 c15 c26"><span class="c11 c14 c32 c16">[Pic]</span></p>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.r19plusv1rnj"></a><span class="c11 c16">Actions</span></h3>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c1 c4"><span>Slideshow (only available if the file is an online editable presentation): Displays the file in presentation mode, opening a new window.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Download: Downloads the file to your local hard drive.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Edit this file (only available if the file is an online editable document or presentation): Takes you to the online editor.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Update file: Allows you to update the selected file. Once you get in there, you may find an option that would let you keep a copy of the old version of the file as well. (This button is only available if you select one single document.)</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Delete: This removes the file from the database</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Archive: Archives the selected file into the Archived Objects folder.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Copy this file: Creates an exact copy of this file.</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.gnijr7hhzf8c"></a><span class="c11 c16">Properties</span></h3>
<ol class="c18" start="1">
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Project: Workspace where this document is allocated to. Clicking on a Project name to select it, takes you to the Documents relating to this Project.</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Created by: User who created this document (including the creation date).</span></li>
<li class="c4 c1"><span>Modified by: User who last modified this document (including the date of the last modification).</span></li>
</ol>
<h3 class="c1 c15 c19"><a name="h.optsb994sd5e"></a><span class="c11 c16">File contents</span></h3>
<p class="c26 c1 c15"><span>If the file you are working with is an online editable document then you get an additional field in the detail view: File contents lets you preview the content of the file without going to edit view.</span></p>
<h2 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.kat8vutoxd33"></a><span class="c11">Document Management</span></h2>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>Like in any collaboration tool you can upload and download documents with Methvin. And like any content object every document has its properties which you can edit. Since you may be familiar with both concepts, managing documents is quite simple.</span></p>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.3h79pg5adaia"></a><span class="c11 c16">Uploading files</span></h3>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>To upload a new file choose “New &gt; Upload a file” in the toolbar.</span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>When uploading a file you have the possibility to give it a new file name and to set all its properties. (You can edit all this at a later stage as well.) Please note the message indicating restrictions around file types and size for upload. (The maximum file is not set by Methvin itself but by some parameters in the php.ini.)</span></p>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.1pe0omk7f3q2"></a><span class="c11 c16">Uploading multiple files</span></h3>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>If you want to upload only a few files the procedure described above is optimal. &nbsp;If you are trying to upload a larger number of files this procedure is time consuming. As an alternative you can pack all files in one single ZIP archive, upload the ZIP archive in the Documents section, an unzip the archive on the server. Archives have a different icon (shown left) and a button to extract the files from the archive (shown right).</span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.pnpdj7b8tcfp"></a><span class="c11 c16">Downloading files</span></h3>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>To download a file go to the detail view of this file, then choose “Download” in the “Actions” menu.</span></p>
<h3 class="c19 c1 c15"><a name="h.e0imhjgiz6cv"></a><span class="c11 c16">Downloading multiple files</span></h3>
<p class="c5 c1"><span>For efficiency, </span><span>pack all files into a ZIP archive by selecting the needed files and clicking the “Compress” button. Note this will be a HUGE file and you may want to consider deleting it from the server once it is downloaded as a ZIP file.</span></p>
<p class="c5 c25 c1">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="c1 c5"><span>PLEASE NOTE: If you are using v1.4.x please make sure that you don't have any links selected when compressing documents since this will lead to an error (which should be fixed in Methvin 1.5).</span><span>1)</span></p>
<h2 class="c21 c1 c15"><a name="h.za6dwagyjdv4"></a><span class="c11">Document editor</span></h2>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>Documents are edited in</span><span>&nbsp;Methvin on line. </span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>[Pic]</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>For clarity in the use of some buttons on the toolbar, use the tooltip which appears when you point on a button and wait a second.</span></p>
<p class="c8 c1"><span>PLEASE NOTE: This editor produces HTML files, not documents in Microsoft Word or OpenOffice.org Writer format. You can download and import them with most word processors, but you can't edit an uploaded *.doc, *.docx or *.odt file. </span></p>
<p class="c8 c25 c1">&nbsp;</p>



